*------------------------------
:SECTION=START_OF_TAPE
* POST VERSION STAMP: hardcoded literal text (no string-literal assignment
* exists in this compiler, so this is a plain :T: line like every other
* static header line here). MUST be bumped by hand every time this .SRC/
* .LIB pair is edited and handed off - this is the only reliable way to
* confirm a posted file actually reflects the latest compiled .ctl, since
* SolidWorks CAM gives no visible compile timestamp. If two outputs that
* are supposed to reflect different source show the SAME version string,
* the .ctl was not actually rebuilt from the edited source - recompile via
* the Post Processor Editor before re-testing.
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:; ###########################################################################<EOL>
:T:;     POST PROCESSOR INFORMATION<EOL>
:T:; ###########################################################################<EOL>
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:; Post Processor Name: SW2026 FrankenOKO GRBL Metric Mill<EOL>
:T:; Author: Compwiser1<EOL>
:T:; Post Version: 1.0.1<EOL>
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:;     PROGRAM OVERVIEW<EOL>
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:; Part Name: <PART_NAME_DISP><EOL>
:T:; Program Number: <"%4LT":(program_number)><EOL>
:T:; Machine Name: <MACHINE_NAME_DISP><EOL>
:T:; Material Type: <MATERIAL_DISP><EOL>
*
* First motion line, split out of START_OF_TAPE so the tool table can be
* printed between the header text and this line (table moved from end of
* tape to under the header per request). Called explicitly right after
* the table in CALC_START_OF_TAPE.
:SECTION=START_OF_TAPE_MOTION
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:; ###########################################################################<EOL>
:T:;     PROGRAM START<EOL>
:T:; ###########################################################################<EOL>
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
* First motion: retract Z to MACHINE home (G28 Z) rather than the old
* G00 Z<clearance> in work coordinates. The old form protected the first
* X/Y rapid from a tool left low (Z-up-before-XY-travel rule), but as an
* ABSOLUTE work-coord target it could also move DOWN (e.g. descending at
* the home corner when the spindle was parked above the clearance
* plane). G91 G28 Z0 is always up-or-stay - same proven idiom used at
* every mid-program tool change (SUB_TOOL_CHANGE_MILL) and program end.
* G00 on the retract line establishes the motion mode the first bare
* X/Y rapid of operation 1 relies on. Per-operation approach order (X/Y
* position first, THEN Z down) is unchanged and already correct.
:T:<N><G:00><G:91><G:28> Z0<EOL>
:T:<N><G:90><G:work_coord><G:21><EOL>
*
:SECTION=INIT_TOOL_CHANGE_MILL
:T:<N><T><M:06><EOL>
:T:<N><S!><M!:SPINDLE_DIR><EOL>
:T:<N><G!:work_coord><EOL>
*
:SECTION=SUB_TOOL_CHANGE_MILL
:T:<N><G:00><G:91><G:28> Z0<EOL>
:T:<N><T><M:06><EOL>
:T:<N><S!><M!:SPINDLE_DIR><EOL>
:T:<N><G!:work_coord><EOL>
*
:SECTION=FIRST_RAPID_Z_MOVE_DOWN_MILL
:T:<N><G:90><G:work_coord><G:00><Z!><EOL>
*
*:SECTION=FIRST_RAPID_Z_PRELOAD_DOWN_MILL
*
*:SECTION=FIVE_AXIS_FIRST_RAPID_Z_DOWN
*
