*
*:SECTION=FASTLINE
*
*:SECTION=FIVE_AXIS_LINE_MOVE_MILL
*
:SECTION=LINE_LEADOUT_MOVE_MILL
:T:<N><G:ABSINC><G:40><G:01><X><Y><Z><F><EOL>
*
:SECTION=ARC_MOVE_MILL
:T:<N><G:ARC_DIR><X><Y><Z><I><J><F><EOL>
*
:SECTION=RADIUS_MOVE_MILL
:T:<N><G:ARC_DIR><X><Y><Z><R><F><attributes><EOL>
*
* Override of the native CALC_RADIAL_ARCS (MILL.LIB ~6880). Two fixes:
* 1) FULL-CIRCLE DETECTION: the native check is exact equality against
*    the FULL_CIRCLE constant - confirmed by real output NOT to match our
*    full circles (they fell through to a single R move with the endpoint
*    suppressed by X/Y modality, producing an invalid bare "G02 R..").
*    Detect instead by tolerance bands: |inc angle| near 360 OR near 0
*    (a genuine 0-degree arc move would never be emitted, so near-0 can
*    only mean a full circle whose angle wrapped to zero).
* 2) QUADRANT SPLIT instead of the native HALF split: a 180-degree
*    R-format arc has chord = exactly 2R, and with output X/Y rounded to
*    1 decimal the printed chord can exceed 2R, making the arc unsolvable
*    (grblHAL error:33). 90-degree arcs have chord ~1.414R - rounding can
*    never push them near the 2R limit. Emits three intermediate quadrant
*    points (via the same trig pattern the native half-split uses) plus
*    the true endpoint = four 90-degree arcs.
* Direction: ARC_DIR already holds the FINAL output direction (set,
* including any ARC_NORM_Z inversion, before CALC_RADIAL_ARCS is
* dispatched in CALC_ARC_MOVE_MILL) - CCW walks +90 per step, CW -90.
:SECTION=CALC_RADIAL_ARCS
:C: QSPLIT_FLAG=0
* SLIVER FILTER: CAMWorks' compensation engine emits micro-arcs (a few
* microns long) at corner transitions - their endpoints display-collapse
* onto their start points at output precision, which in I/J mode printed
* as bare "G02 I.. J.." (a FULL-CIRCLE command to grbl - a latent gouge
* bug that also existed in the original I/J post, never triggered only
* because the lead-in error:33 always halted execution first). Any arc
* shorter than ~0.05mm (R*angle_deg < 3) is below what the output format
* can even represent - suppress it entirely; the next absolute move
* re-syncs position. DO NOT re-route these into the full-circle split:
* that exact mistake (treating near-zero angles as wrapped full circles)
* turned every corner sliver into a real cut circle in v2026.07.12-B -
* caught in code review before it reached the machine.
:C: IF (ARC_RADIUS*(ABS(ARC_INC_ANGLE)))<3 THEN RETURN ENDIF
:C: IF (ABS(ARC_INC_ANGLE))=FULL_CIRCLE THEN QSPLIT_FLAG=1 ENDIF
:C: IF (ABS(ARC_INC_ANGLE))>359.99 THEN QSPLIT_FLAG=1 ENDIF
:C: IF QSPLIT_FLAG=1 THEN GOTO1 ENDIF
:C: IF SECTIONEXIST(RADIUS_MOVE_MILL) THEN
:C: CALL(RADIUS_MOVE_MILL)
:C: ENDIF
:C: RETURN
*
*    360 circle: split into four 90-degree quadrant arcs
*
:C1: IF ARC_DIR=GC(G_CCW_ARC) THEN QSPLIT_STEP=90 ELSE QSPLIT_STEP=(-90) ENDIF
:C: QSPLIT_COUNT=1
:C2: IF QSPLIT_COUNT<4 THEN
:C: QSPLIT_ANG=(ARC_START_ANGLE+(QSPLIT_STEP*QSPLIT_COUNT))
:C: X_POS=(ABS_I_CENTER+(ARC_RADIUS*(COS(((QSPLIT_ANG/180)*PI)))))
:C: Y_POS=(ABS_J_CENTER+(ARC_RADIUS*(SIN(((QSPLIT_ANG/180)*PI)))))
:C:    IF SECTIONEXIST(RADIUS_MOVE_MILL) THEN
:C:    CALL(RADIUS_MOVE_MILL)
:C:    ENDIF
:C: QSPLIT_COUNT=(QSPLIT_COUNT+1)
:C: GOTO2
:C: ENDIF
:C: X_POS=ABS_X_END
:C: Y_POS=ABS_Y_END
:C: IF SECTIONEXIST(RADIUS_MOVE_MILL) THEN
:C: CALL(RADIUS_MOVE_MILL)
:C: ENDIF
:C: RETURN
