:SECTION=CALC_CHECK_OPER_COMMENTS
* Overridden. Two real bugs found from testing needed fixing here:
* 1. Duplicate headers (6 shown for 4 real SOLIDWORKS CAM operations) -
*    this section gets called MORE THAN ONCE for a single logical
*    operation (once per internal CAMWorks sub-segment, e.g. multi-
*    location counterbore features). The native GET_OPER_COMMENTS
*    apparently had built-in de-duplication that got lost when bypassed
*    entirely. Fixed by skipping this whole section if the operation name
*    matches the immediately-preceding call - a reasonable heuristic given
*    the confirmed pattern (exact name repeats with no different operation
*    between them), though it would incorrectly merge two genuinely
*    separate operations that happen to share an identical name back-to-
*    back - flagging this trade-off, not claiming it's airtight.
* 2. Notes always showing "None" - bypassing GET_OPER_COMMENTS entirely
*    apparently also lost whatever populates OPR_COMMENT with the actual
*    notes text (its likely real job, not just conditionally gating our
*    callback). Restored the native call. GOT_NOTES flag (set inside
*    CALC_OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT) detects whether GET_OPER_COMMENTS actually
*    fired our callback (meaning real notes existed) - if not, we know
*    notes were genuinely empty and manually trigger the "None" path
*    ourselves, fixing the original missing-header bug without losing
*    notes population for operations that DO have them.
* 3. Duplicate headers, take two: found via diagnostic testing that
*    PREV_OPER_NAME was silently truncating around 26 chars without an
*    explicit ATTRINLEN (see .LIB), breaking the comparison for longer
*    operation names like "Counter Bores For Mounting Screws" (34 chars) -
*    the truncated copy never equaled the full current name, so the
*    de-dup check never fired for names longer than the truncation point.
:C: IF TLP_OPER_NAME=PREV_OPER_NAME THEN RETURN ENDIF
:C: PREV_OPER_NAME=TLP_OPER_NAME
:C: OP_NUM=(OP_NUM+1)
:C: GOT_NOTES=0
:C: GET_OPER_COMMENTS(CALC_OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT)
:C: IF GOT_NOTES=0 THEN
:C: CALL(CALC_SET_COOLANT)
:C: CALL(OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT_NO_NOTES)
:C: ENDIF
*
:SECTION=CALC_OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT
:C: GOT_NOTES=1
:C: CALL(CALC_SET_COOLANT)
:C: CALL(OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT_WITH_NOTES)
*
:SECTION=CALC_SET_COOLANT
* Fixes Flood/Mist coolant not reflecting the per-operation Coolant
* dropdown in SOLIDWORKS CAM. Root cause (confirmed by tracing MILL.LIB
* directly): CL_COOLANT_TYPE (the real per-operation value CAM sets from
* that dropdown) is only ever applied for Gun Drilling cycles
* (CALC_OUTPUT_COOLANT, gated by OPR_TYPE=MILL_DRILLING AND
* OPR_DRILL_CYCLE_TYPE=GUN_DRILLING - and that whole section is otherwise
* dead code, never called for normal milling). Every other operation type
* falls back to a fixed, post-wide "coolant" setting (ATTRTYPE=SELECT, a
* Post Processor Setup dropdown, NOT the per-operation one) - that's why
* Flood never showed up regardless of what was picked per-operation.
* This override reads CL_COOLANT_TYPE for every operation type, mapping
* 1=Off, 2=Flood, 3=Mist to MC(M_COOL_OFF)/MC(M_COOL_FLOOD)/
* MC(M_COOL_MIST) - confirmed M9/M8/M7 respectively via the M-code group
* defaults. Shared between both the "has notes" and "no notes" paths so
* the coolant logic only lives in one place.
:C: NEW_COOLANT=COOLANT_TYPE
:C: IF CL_COOLANT_TYPE=1 THEN NEW_COOLANT=MC(M_COOL_OFF) ENDIF
:C: IF CL_COOLANT_TYPE=2 THEN NEW_COOLANT=MC(M_COOL_FLOOD) ENDIF
:C: IF CL_COOLANT_TYPE=3 THEN NEW_COOLANT=MC(M_COOL_MIST) ENDIF
* Force an explicit M9 whenever switching between two DIFFERENT ACTIVE
* coolant states (Flood<->Mist), guaranteeing both are never considered
* on at once. Not needed when coming from Off/uninitialized (nothing was
* on) or going TO Off (that's already a single M9).
:C: IF NEW_COOLANT<>PREV_COOLANT THEN
:C:    IF PREV_COOLANT<>0 AND PREV_COOLANT<>MC(M_COOL_OFF) AND NEW_COOLANT<>MC(M_COOL_OFF) THEN
:C:    COOLANT_TYPE=MC(M_COOL_OFF)
:C:    CALL(FORCE_COOLANT_OFF)
:C:    ENDIF
:C: ENDIF
:C: PREV_COOLANT=NEW_COOLANT
:C: COOLANT_TYPE=NEW_COOLANT
*
:SECTION=FORCE_COOLANT_OFF
:T:<N><M!:COOLANT_TYPE><EOL>
*
:SECTION=OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT_NO_NOTES
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:;    Operation Summary<EOL>
:T:;     - Description: <OPER_NAME_DISP><EOL>
:T:;     - Notes: None<EOL>
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:<N><M!:COOLANT_TYPE><EOL>
*
:SECTION=OUTPUT_OPER_COMMENT_WITH_NOTES
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:;    Operation Summary<EOL>
:T:;     - Description: <OPER_NAME_DISP><EOL>
:T:;     - Notes: <OPR_COMMENT_DISP><EOL>
:T:; ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<EOL>
:T:<N><M!:COOLANT_TYPE><EOL>
*
*:SECTION=CHANGE_MILL_SPEED
*
*:SECTION=OUTPUT_DWELL
*
*:SECTION=OUTPUT_COOLANT
*
:SECTION=BEFORE_ATTRIBUTES
:T:<N><G:ABSINC><EOL>
:T:<N><attributes><EOL>
*
:SECTION=AFTER_ATTRIBUTES
:T:<N><G:ABSINC><EOL>
:T:<N><attributes><EOL>
*
:SECTION=program_stop
:T:<M:00><EOL>
*
:SECTION=optional_stop
:T:<M:01><EOL>
